          "props": {
            "command": "The framing that the i rotates the time-derivative term ninety degrees so the equation interferes instead of diffusing is what I want to test with my own hands. Help me: (1) take a single plane-wave and plug it into the equation with and without the i to see oscillation versus runaway spreading, (2) show explicitly how the i keeps the total probability fixed at one and links to the Born rule, and (3) explain what physically breaks about atoms if probability were allowed to leak out of a region.",
            "topic": "QUANTUM MECHANICS",
