    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "t_start": 0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "An electron, released in free space. Watch what happens next.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "QUANTUM MECHANICS",
        "headline": "Why the i in Schrodinger's Equation Changes Everything",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 3.71,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "t_start": 7,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Two equations. Nearly identical. One describes a wave — it travels, breathes, stays sharp. The other describes heat: it spreads and never comes back.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "Create"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.1,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "t_start": 17,
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "The only difference between them is a single letter. Remove the i from Schrodinger's equation and the quantum world stops being a wave.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "Transform"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.42,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 26,
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "One imaginary unit. Why does it decide whether quantum mechanics is even possible?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE QUESTION",
        "headline": "Two equations differ by one factor of i. One propagates a wave. One spreads heat. Why does that single symbol decide whether quantum mechanics works at all?",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 4.62,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "t_start": 34,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The diffusion equation governs heat, ink in water, any spreading process. A blob of heat placed here moves outward and never contracts. That is irreversible.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "Create"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.33,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "t_start": 45,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "A classical particle thrown in a direction stays on that trajectory. A reasonable person would expect a quantum particle to do the same.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "STILL",
        "source": "ai",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "A classical particle thrown in a direction stays on that trajectory.…",
            "eyebrow": "",
            "topic": "QUANTUM MECHANICS"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B06.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.89,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "t_start": 55,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "But if you write the Schrodinger equation without the i, the electron packet dissolves instantly. No trajectory. Just a smear that widens forever.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "animate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.8,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "t_start": 66,
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "So what does the i actually do?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE MECHANISM",
        "headline": "What the i actually does",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 1.67,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "t_start": 73,
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "narration_text": "Without the i, both the time derivative and the space derivative pull the wavefunction in the same direction — they add and push amplitude outward. That is diffusion.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "animate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.93,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "t_start": 86,
      "estimated_duration_s": 14,
      "narration_text": "The i rotates the time-derivative contribution ninety degrees in the complex plane. Now the two terms interfere instead of adding. The amplitude oscillates and travels.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "Rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.16,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "t_start": 100,
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "That rotation keeps the total probability exactly one — the i is the keeper of the Born rule.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE MECHANISM",
        "headline": "The i keeps probability from leaking away",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 5.98,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B11.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B11.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "t_start": 107,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Without the i, probability leaks out of any region. Atoms could not be stable. Interference fringes could not form. Spectral lines would not exist.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "animate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.69,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B12.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B12.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "t_start": 118,
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "The i is not an algebraic convenience. It is what makes quantum mechanics physically possible.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE IMPLICATION",
        "headline": "The i is not optional",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B13.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 5.69,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B13.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B13.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B14",
      "t_start": 126,
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "A worked example with illustrative numbers.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "THE EXAMPLE",
        "headline": "An electron in a 1 nm pocket",
        "dek": "(illustrative)"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B14.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 2.35,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B14.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B14.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B15",
      "t_start": 134,
      "estimated_duration_s": 18,
      "narration_text": "Release an electron from a 1-nanometer pocket. Diffusion version: width hits 10 nanometers in 3 femtoseconds — gone. Schrodinger version: a coherent pulse crosses a 5-nanometer gap and arrives at a detector intact. Same packet. One letter makes the difference.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "animate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B15.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 18.42,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-schrodinger-i/clips/B15.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B15.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B16",
      "t_start": 152,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Remove the i: wave becomes heat, spreading forever. Keep it: amplitude propagates coherently. One symbol. That is why quantum mechanics exists.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "card": {
        "eyebrow": "QUANTUM MECHANICS",
        "headline": "Remove the i: wave becomes heat, spreading forever. Keep it: amplitude propagates coherently. The i is why quantum mechanics exists.",
        "dek": ""
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-schrodinger-i/mp3/beat-B16.mp3",
